      <section eId="sec_CC-3107">
        <num>CC 3107</num>
        <heading>3107. Â Capacity of arbitrators</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-3107__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>All persons may be arbitrators, except such as are under some incapacity or infirmity, which renders them unfit for that function.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3107__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Therefore, minors under the age of eighteen years, persons interdicted, those who are deaf and unable to speak, can not be arbitrators.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110154</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
